# Collabhost stage instance contract -- the TOLD INPUTS for deploy-stage.sh (card #443).
#
# Theo's one-time box stand-up writes the real file at /etc/collabhost-stage/instance.env,
# root-owned and READABLE BY THE stage-deploy USER (e.g. 0640 root:stage-deploy). The
# deploy script + seed source it; every writable location is told here, never discovered
# (Standard Hosting rule #1). A missing required key fails the deploy LOUD (rule #4) --
# the script never guesses an isolation value.
#
# This .example is the reconcile artifact between Remy's deploy half and Theo's box half:
# the key set the script REQUIRES. Decision #2 is alt-ports :8080/:8443 + internal CA;
# the base domain is stage.collab.internal (see card #443). The stage-tree paths + the
# service are owned by Theo's root-owned `stage-privop` helper (it hardcodes them); the
# keys below are the ones the UNPRIVILEGED deploy/seed scripts still read directly --
# build inputs, the control-plane URL + admin-key file, and the wipe-guard's denylist.
# Copy, fill in the real admin-key file path + RID, and adjust paths to the box.

# ---- Privileged helper --------------------------------------------------------
# The single root-owned helper every privileged op routes through (sudo stage-privop
# <verb>). Default shown; only set to override for local authoring.
#STAGE_PRIVOP=/opt/collabhost-stage/deploy/stage-privop

# ---- Build-on-box root (stage-deploy-owned) -----------------------------------
# The deploy checks out to $STAGE_BUILD_ROOT/checkout and publishes to
# $STAGE_BUILD_ROOT/publish -- the build-output paths Theo's install-artifacts /
# install-caddy verbs read. stage-deploy-owned, 0755 dirs; the build runs here
# unprivileged.
STAGE_BUILD_ROOT=/home/stage-deploy/build
STAGE_REPO_URL=https://github.com/MrBildo/collabhost.git
# git remote name inside the checkout (default: origin)
#STAGE_GIT_REMOTE=origin

# ---- Build target -------------------------------------------------------------
# The box RID. linux-x64 or linux-arm64 -- decides `dotnet publish -r` (and, for
# STAGE_CADDY_SOURCE=build, the Caddy cross-compile target via build-caddy.sh).
STAGE_RID=linux-x64

# Bundled Caddy: build (mirror the prod publish from the ref's pins -- exercises a
# caddy.version bump on stage; needs Go on the box) | copy (prod's bundled caddy --
# zero Go toolchain, but does not test the ref's Caddy). Default: build.
STAGE_CADDY_SOURCE=build
PROD_CADDY_PATH=/opt/collabhost/bin/caddy

# Wipe the internal CA on a clean deploy too (privop wipe-ca; regenerates certs --
# the box must then re-trust stage's CA). Default 0 -- keep the CA so the one-time
# "trust the stage CA" step from stand-up survives wipes.
#STAGE_WIPE_CADDY=0

# ---- Control plane (the seed registers against this) --------------------------
STAGE_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:58500
# The stage admin key lives in a 0600 file owned by stage-deploy (NOT inline here).
# The same key the stage unit boots with (COLLABHOST_ADMIN_KEY); v1.8.0 requires the
# Administrator role for registration, which this key carries. The seed reads it.
STAGE_ADMIN_KEY_FILE=/home/stage-deploy/.stage-admin-key

# Readiness wait + optional through-proxy smoke (warn-only; depends on stage DNS /
# edge-bind, which is Theo's half). e.g. https://demo-dotnet-api.stage.collab.internal:8443
#STAGE_READY_TIMEOUT=90
#STAGE_SMOKE_APP_URL=

# ---- Stage state dirs (the wipe-guard pre-flight denylist check) --------------
# These MUST mirror the dirs Theo's `stage-privop wipe-data` / `wipe-ca` hardcode.
# The deploy does not pass them to the wipe (the helper hardcodes its targets); it
# validates them with assert_wipe_target before invoking the path-less verb, so a
# typo that named a prod path is caught in-script. collabhost-stage-owned.
STAGE_DATA_ROOT=/var/lib/collabhost-stage
STAGE_DATA=/var/lib/collabhost-stage/data
STAGE_APP_DATA=/var/lib/collabhost-stage/app-data
STAGE_CADDY_STORAGE=/var/lib/collabhost-stage/caddy
STAGE_SRV=/srv/stage

# ---- Prod anchors (the wipe guard's denylist) ---------------------------------
# Named so assert_wipe_target can refuse to touch prod even on an env typo. Belt-and-
# suspenders atop the kernel perms (stage user can't write prod) + the prod-pathless
# sudoers (Theo's dispatcher half).
PROD_DATA=/var/lib/collabhost
PROD_PREFIX=/opt/collabhost
PROD_CONFIG_DIR=/etc/collabhost
